types.section:
{{fr-intj}}

# {{lb|fr|telephone}} [[hello]] (when answering at the beginning of a call)
# {{lb|fr|telephone}} used to confirm that the person being addressed is listening, or to confirm if anyone is listening
#: {{uxi|fr|'''Allô'''? Tu m'entends?|t='''Hello'''? You hear me?}}
# {{lb|fr|North America}} [[hello]] (as an in-person greeting)
# {{lb|fr|informal}} [[hello]]! (implying someone is not paying attention to the obvious)

====Usage notes====
* Using "allô" as a greeting is normal in Quebec, New England, Louisiana and Missouri.
* In some online communities, instead of saying "hey" or "hi" or "wsg" (what's good), you might say "alo" when joining a chatroom.

